## Overview

GeoAssist is a reusable, configuration-driven framework that leverages **Databricks Foundation Models** to automatically detect and correct geographic data quality issues.

Instead of maintaining thousands of mapping rules and lookup tables, GeoAssist uses **Llama 3.3 70B** to intelligently validate and standardize geographic values.

### Example

| Input | Output |
|---------|---------|
| Mumbay | Mumbai |
| Chenai | Chennai |
| New Yrok | New York |
| Untied Kingdom | United Kingdom |
| Germaany | Germany |

---

## Architecture

```text
Raw Data
   │
   ▼
Bronze Layer
   │
   ▼
Geo Validator
(Llama 3.3 70B)
   │
   ▼
Confidence Scoring
   │
   ├── High Confidence
   ├── Medium Confidence
   └── Low Confidence

```


## 🚀 Quick Start

### Configure Columns

```python
TARGET_COLUMNS = [
    "city",
    "state",
    "country"
]
```

### Configure Input File

```python
INPUT_FILE = "/Volumes/geo_assist/raw/geo_assist/airports.dat.txt"
```

### Run

```text
01_bronze.ipynb
      ↓
validator.ipynb


